but only the Mind that they conceiv'd it to be indu'd with. And then, for their Reaſon diffus'd thorough every Nature, they underſtood by it a Spirit, that took a ſeveral Name according to the various Mutations of the Matter it paſs'd thorough; that it accommodated its Operations to the Matter; but that its Principality was in the Sky. The ſame Stoiques held God to be One; only they aſſign'd him ſeveral Appellations, according to his various Faculties, or Offices.

